<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kohl Pledges Strong Single Currency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 27 (Xinhua) -- German Chancellor Helmut Kohl today
repeated his pledges that the planned single European currency,
the Euro, must meet the strict stability criteria.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a construction project in Berlin today, Kohl
dismissed any suggestion that he would sacrifice the strength of
the Euro for the sake of the total European integration project.
</P>
<P>
"That is a price I will not pay," he said.
</P>
<P>
He added he would hold on to the Euro stability criteria and
its timetable.
</P>
<P>
The European Union (EU) is due to launch the Euro on January 1,
1999. Countries which want to join the club are required, among
other things, to bring their budget deficit and national debt to
less than 3 percent and 60 percent respectively of the gross
domestic product (GDP). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
