<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Seminar Commemorates Late General Su Yu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 27 (Xinhua) -- A seminar was held here today to
commemorate the brilliant military record of Su Yu, a former
high-ranking general in the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA).
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin, who is also chairman of the
Central Military Committee and general secretary of the Communist
Party of China Central Committee, wrote an inscription for the
seminar, praising the general for his perfect command of the
military principles of Chairman Mao Zedong and his ability to use
surprise tactics to defeat enemies.
</P>
<P>
Su Yu (1907-1984) led his troops in major battles against
Japanese invaders, and later against Kuomintang reactionary
troops. He was promoted to the rank of major general of the PLA
after the founding of the People's Republic.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Zhen, Zhang Wannian, and Chi Haotian, vice-chairmen of
the Central Military Committee, were among those attending the
seminar.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the seminar, Zhang Zhen said that Su's concepts
concerning the rules of modern warfare are still fully applicable
to the study of the tactics and theory of war.
</P>
<P>
He also urged that army officers and soldiers alike to fulfill
their duties by rallying closely around the CPC Central Committee
and the Central Military Commission with Jiang Zemin at the core.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
