<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fiber Optic Network Market Booming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The international fiber optic
network market is expected to amount to 25 billion U.S. dollars in
the next five years, a U.S. consulting firm said today.
</P>
<P>
A total of 289,000 km of submarine fiber optic cable worth of
15.32 billion dollars and 127,000 km of terrestrial fiber optic
cable valued at 9.53 billion dollars are forecast to be deployed
from 1998-2002, it said.
</P>
<P>
The Massachusetts-based Cambridge Pioneer Consulting said
networks interconnecting nations or continents are being deployed
to meet the needs of data and video services which are expanding
at annual rates of 85 percent to 95 percent per year in all
regions of the globe.
</P>
<P>
The assessment excludes domestic fiber deployments, a market
which is also growing at rates over 20 percent yearly, the firm
said in a report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
