<HEADLINE> Iraq Suggests Joint Search for Missing Saudi Pilot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Iraq has suggested a joint
search with Saudi Arabia for a missing Saudi pilot lost in the
1991 Gulf war, an official spokesman said here today.
</P>
<P>
But Saudi Arabia, which sided with western powers against Iraq
in the war, has doubted Iraq's intentions behind the suggestion,
the official Iraqi News Agency (INA) quoted the spokesman as
saying.
</P>
<P>
However, the spokesman said, Baghdad is still waiting for a
reply from Saudi Arabia to the suggestion.
</P>
<P>
The suggestion was made at a time when Iraq has been seeking
rapprochement with neighbors, observers said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said Iraqi searchers looking for missing Kuwaitis
and Saudi Arabians lost during the war have spotted the wreckage
of a Saudi warplane. But the pilot was found missing, believed to
have died, he added.
</P>
<P>
Iraq informed Saudi Arabia immediately through the
International Committee of the Red Cross (ICRC) and suggested
forming a technical team headed by an ICRC official and including
representatives from Iraq and Saudi Arabia, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
