<HEADLINE> Pakistan to Implement New Investment Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The Pakistani government will
soon announce an investment policy to attract both domestic and
foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed today by Humayun Akhtar, chairman of the
Board of Investment, while addressing a conference of members of
All Pakistan Textile Mills Association (APTMA) in Pakistan's
southern port city of Karachi, according to the official
Associated Press of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Akhtar said efforts were being made under the leadership of
Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif to look into problems facing the local
and foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
"We intend to introduce one-window operation at the Board of
Investment to facilitate and guide investors," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also asked the APTMA members to suggest ways and means to
attract foreign investment in the textile sector and promote joint
venture projects.  
</P>
</TEXT>
