<HEADLINE> Saudi Arabia Raps Israeli Raids on Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia, one of the
heavyweights in the Arab world, today reiterated its strong
condenmation of the Israeli raids against south Lebanon, reports
reaching here said today.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Second Deputy Prime Minister, Minister of Defense
Prince Sultan Ibn Abdul-Aziz said the raids were "Israeli crimes
against a peaceful people," according to official Saudi Press
Agency.
</P>
<P>
During its session Monday, which was chaired by King Fahd Bin
Abdel Aziz, the Saudi cabinet condemned the Israeli raids and
described them as "flagrant violation of international laws and
norms."
</P>
<P>
Israel has lately launched a wave of attacks against targets
in south Lebanon and its troops killed three Hezbollah (Party of
God) guerrillas Saturday in fierce clashes that included air raids
and artillery exchange.
</P>
<P>
The violence capped the worst week in south Lebanon's
cross-border violence since a cease-fire understanding between
Israel and Lebanon ended a 17-day Israeli blitz on Lebanon in
April 1996.
</P>
<P>
About 2,000 Israeli troops have held a border occupation in a
self-declared "security zone" in south Lebanon since 1985, in
defiance of U.N. resolutions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
