<HEADLINE> Ukrainian Wins Men's 800 Meters Freestyle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MESSINA, Sicily, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Igor Snitko of Ukraine won
the title of the men's 800 meters freestyle at the Universiade here on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Snitko's winning time of 8:05.13 was 0.33 seconds slower than the
Universiade record set by Turlough O'Hare of Canada at the 1993
Buffalo Universiade.
</P>
<P>
Luiz Eduardo Lima of Brazil took the silver medal at 8:06.26,
followed by Marco Formentini of Italy in the third place at 8:06.37.
</P>
