<HEADLINE> Karpov Wins Simultaneous Game with Chinese Players </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 27 (Xinhua) -- World chess champion Anatoly
Karpov of Russia wrapped up his first simultaneous games of the
China tour against six local women players with four wins and two
draws here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The 46-year-old Russian was challenged by half a dozen Chinese
top women nationals except Xie Jun, former women world champion,
in the friendly exhibition. The time limit was two hours.
</P>
<P>
The experienced grandmaster underlined his world champion
status by beating the Chinese with ease. He first got better of
Zhu Chen, world youth champion, and then rolled over Wang Ping,
Qin Kanying and Xu Yuhua soon.
</P>
<P>
But Wang Lei and Ning Chunhong posed some opposition to the
world champion and finished their games with draws.
</P>
<P>
After the match, Karpov highly appraised the Chinese girls,
especially Wang Lei and Ning Chunhong, who quickly attacked the
errors he made.
</P>
<P>
Karpov will play against 16 Chinese junior players
simultaneously on August 30. 
</P>
</TEXT>
