<HEADLINE> Plague Outbreaks in Central Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Plague spread by marmots has
claimed two human lives in central Mongolia and forced the local
authorities to seal off the area.
</P>
<P>
The official Montsame news agency reported today that 74 people
who had contacts with the dead have been isolated and more than
170 others suspected to have been infected by the plague have been
put under hospital monitoring.
</P>
<P>
The epidemic has also been reported in other parts of the
country. 
</P>
