<DOCNO> XIE19970828.0020 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Domestic Conflict Breeds Crime: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Delinquency is associated with
family discord, poor parental supervision and harsh or erratic
discipline, said a report today, calling for support for the
family in order to cut crime.
</P>
<P>
The report, by the National Association for the Care and
Resettlement of Offenders, said that evidence suggests a link
between broken homes and delinquency, but children brought up by
loving lone parents may be less likely to offend than those raised
by feuding couples.
</P>
<P>
The report surveyed more than 5,300 UK children born in 1946
and found that they were much more likely to commit serious
offenses if their parents separated before they were four, and
rates of offending were twice those among children whose parents
stayed together.
</P>
<P>
However, this only applied to children whose parents separated
because of conflict as offending rose only slightly among those
who lost a parent through death or long-term hospitalization, said
the report.
</P>
<P>
"A strategy to target the needs of young families will do far
more to cut crime than tough sentencing, tagging, curfews or more
prisons," said Paul Cavadino, principal officer of the
association. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970828.0021 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tripartite Protocol Signed to Improve TAZARA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 27 (Xinhua) -- China, Tanzania and Zambia today
signed a new technical cooperation protocol here to improve the
operation of the Tanzania-Zambia railway authorities known as
TAZARA.
</P>
<P>
Sun Guangxiang, visiting Assistant Minister of the Chinese Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation Ministry, Zambia's Acting
Transport Minister, Mines Minister Christon Tembo and Tanzanian
Transport Minister William Kusila signed the protocol separately
on behalf of their own government.
</P>
<P>
Before signing the protocol they held a tripartite talks on
how to continue the cooperation, improve management and
efficiency and enhance competitiveness of the 1860-kilometre
railway.
</P>
<P>
In the talks Tembo expressed his gratude to China for its
persistent technical and financial assistance to TAZARA and said
that Zambia and Tanzania is committed to improving its management
and operation and ensure its survival and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Kusila said that TAZARA is currently operating in a very
competivie environment which calls for aggressive marketing,
adminstering competitive tariffs and improving efficiency in its
operations.
</P>
<P>
The Tanzanian minister said that one of the problems facing
the TAZARA is poor management, which has led to the poor
operational performance of the railway.
</P>
<P>
Sun Guangxiang briefed the participants on the implementation
of the phase-eight technical cooperation, which will expires at
the end of this year, and made suggestions for the next phase
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said the low traffic has been a serious handicap on the
railway's way of growth.
</P>
<P>
A change in poitical and economic situation in recent years in
southern Africa and the subsequent battle for market share
among various sources and modes of transportation combined with a
year-on-year decline in Zambian copper production have reduced the
annual traffic of the TAZARA, he added.
</P>
<P>
Sun stressed the importance of better management and bringing
the existing equipment into full play.
</P>
<P>
He called for improved rail service and a target-based
manangement responsibility system, the more effective and
vigorous rules and regulations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
