<HEADLINE> USAID to Keep on Funding Southern Africa's Rural </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The United States Aid Agency
(USAID) today announced that southern Africa's community-based
natural resources management program (NBNRM) has been approved
for funding by the United States.
</P>
<P>
An official of the USAID regional office for southern Africa
said the program had been included in the long term strategy, but
he did not mention the amount involved.
</P>
<P>
The assistance for the program will continue up to 1999 after
which a new agreement will have to be negotiated.
</P>
<P>
The official was addressing a five-day NBNRM conference which
opened in Victoria Falls Town on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The conference, expected to come up with a southern African
plan of action for the natural resources program, is being
attended by more than 200 delegates who include rural community
representatives, chiefs, parliamentarians and environmental
experts.
</P>
<P>
The NBNRM program entails sustainable use of resources to
benefit local rural communities.
</P>
<P>
The sustainable approach has yielded positive results and
significantly raised the standards of living of the rural poor.
