<HEADLINE> Annan Appoints Assistant Secretary-General for Human </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 27 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan today appointed Mrs. Rafiah Salim of Malaysia as
assistant secretary-general for human resources management.
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Calim, whose appointment will be effective on October 15,
1997, will succeed Danis Halliday who is taking up his appointment
as humanitarian coordinator of the oil for food program on
September 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Salim has been assistant governor at the Bank Negara
Malaysia since 1995, responsible for human resources management
and legal affairs. Between 1991 and 1995 she worked as general
manager, Human Resource Department, of the Malayan Banking Berhad.
</P>
<P>
As general manager, she introduced and implemented improvements
relating to performance of management, computer systems for human
resources management, as well as handing industrial relations,
welfare activities of employees and development programs and
training. 
</P>
</TEXT>
