<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chernomyrdin Meets With Liu Huaqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Development of relations with
China in the political, economic and other fields is Russia's
priority foreign policy, Russian Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin said here today.
</P>
<P>
While meeting with Vice Chairman of the Central Military
Commission of China Liu Huaqing, Chernomyrdin expressed
satisfaction with the development of Russian-Chinese relations.
"The Russian-Chinese relations in all fields are in good state and
they are better than any time before," he said.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin noted that very good relations have taken shape
between the top leaders of the two countries. "It plays an active
role in promoting Russian-Chinese relations," he said.
</P>
<P>
Russia is making serious preparation for the forthcoming visit
of President Boris Yeltsin to Beijing, which will carry the
friendly relations between the two countries to a new stage, the
Russian premier said.
</P>
<P>
Liu Huaqing, for his part, said the Chinese government and
leadership attach importance to the development of Chinese-Russian
relations of friendship.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese and Russian leaders raised the bilateral relations
to a new stage with the creation of the strategic partnership
between the two countries oriented towards the 21st century, Liu
said. The further development of Chinese-Russian relations has a
constructive meaning to peace and stability in the two countries
and to the two peoples, he added.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, Liu Huaqing conveyed cordial greetings from
Chairman Jiang Zemin and Premier Li Peng to President Boris
Yeltsin and Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin, and Chernomyrdin
passed cordial greetings through Liu Huaqing to Chairman Jiang
Zemin and Premier Li Peng.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin meanwhile expressed best wishes to the Chinese
leadership on the upcoming convening of the 15th congress of the
Chinese Communist Party. He told Liu, "We wish you greater
successes in developing the economy and raising the people's
living level."
</P>
<P>
Later today, Chinese Ambassador in Moscow Li Fenglin, in the
name of Liu Huaqing, held a return banquet at the Chinese embassy
in honor of Russian officials. The banquet was attended by Russian
Vice Prime Minister Yakov Urinson and other officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
