<HEADLINE> Annan Appoints Force Commander of UNIFIL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 27 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan today appointed Major-General Jioje Konousi Konrote of
Fiji as the next force commander of the United Nations Interim
Force in Lebanon (UNIFIL) with effect from October 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Major-General Konrote will succeed Major-General Stanislaw
Franciszek Wozmak of Poland who has served as commander from April
1995 and will leave his post on September 30, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Major-General Konrote has served in the Fijian armed forces
since 1996. He received his military training in New Zealand and
Australia and is a graduate of the Australian College of Defense
and Strategic Studies. He is currently chief of staff and deputy
commander of the Republic of Fiji Military Forces.
</P>
<P>
Major-Commander Konrote has extensive experience with the
UNIFIL, where he served five times, as company commander
(1978, 1980-81), senior plans officer at the UNIFIL Headquarters
(1983-84), battalion commander (1986-87), and deputy force
commander (1990-91). 
</P>
</TEXT>
