<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chirac Proposes Franco-American Initiative in Mideast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 27 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
today proposed that France and the United States make a joint
initiative in the Middle East to save the peace process from dying
out completely.
</P>
<P>
Chirac also expressed his hope to improve relations with
Algeria, which so far has failed to come out of the cycle of
violence between the government and Islamic militants.
</P>
<P>
"In the Middle East where the peace process is in danger of
death, where despair breeds violence and terrorism, France should
take the initiative, in liaison with the United States," said
Chirac at a conference of French ambassadors stationed abroad.
</P>
<P>
He said that Europe, with its shared history with the Middle
East, its political importance and economic power, should be
engaged in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
Chirac also said that the Mediterranean region should be a
place of "peace, stability and development."
</P>
<P>
"France is a Mediterranean power. It should first maintain with
the Magreb countries a model relationship. This is the case with
Morocco and Tunisia. It should be the case -- I hope -- with
Algeria," said Chirac. 
</P>
</TEXT>
