<HEADLINE> China Wins Second Diving Gold at Universiade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MESSINA, Sicily, August 27 (Xinhua) -- China won its second gold
medal at the University Games diving tournament through Zhu Jinhong in
the women's 3-meter springboard on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Zhu, who took part in the 1988 Seoul Olympic Games, totalled 507.57
points for the title. Lu Haisong, who won the women's 1-meter
springboard for China on Monday, finished second at 493.47, followed
by veteran Mexican Maria Jo Alcala Izguerra in the third place at
479.40.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Jinhong suffered from a slow start in the preliminaries and was
nearly eliminated as she only qualified for the semi-finals as the
17th placed diver.
</P>
<P>
But in the afternoon's semi-finals, Zhu turned to the best diver as
she collected a total of 210.09 points from 5 dives.
</P>
<P>
In the evening's final, Zhu maintained her form well and scored a
match-high of 69.72 points from her fourth dive, a backword two and a
half samersaults at pike position.
</P>
<P>
Lu Haisong, who led after the third dive in the final, faulted with
her fourth dive and got only 52.20 points.
</P>
<P>
Though Zhu Jinhong chose an easier dive with lower degree of
difficulty in the last round, she still managed to get 51.75 points
for a winning total of 507.57. 
</P>
</TEXT>
