<HEADLINE> Liberia's Taylor Arrives for ECOWAS Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABUJA, Nigeria, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Liberian new President
Charles Taylor arrived tonight in the Nigerian capital here for
Thursday's summit of heads of states of the Economic Community of
West African States (ECOWAS).
</P>
<P>
The annual summit will focus on how to get Sierra Leone's
military junta to give up power they seized in a widely
condemned coup on May 25.
</P>
<P>
Taylor was greeted at the Abuja Hilton Hotel by a group of
Liberians who identified themselves as the Nigerian chapter of
Taylor's National Patriotic Party.
</P>
<P>
Some of them came from the refugee camp in Oru, Ogun State in
Nigeria, according to an official from the Liberian embassy in
Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
Burkina Faso President Blaise Compraore, Togolese President
Gnassingbe Eyadema, Mali President Alpha Oumar Konare and
President of the Benin Republic Mathieu Kerekou also arrived in
Abuja earlier this evening for the 16-member ECOWAS summit.
</P>
