<HEADLINE> China Miss Golden Chance of Winning Fencing Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Sicily, August 27 (Xinhua) -- China squandered a golden
chance of winning their first fencing gold at the Universiade and had
to be settled with a bronze on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese women's epee team lost to Russia by a small margin of
45-42 in the semi-finals and had to fight for the third place against
Germany.
</P>
<P>
They beat the Germans 45-32 in the playoff and won the bronze
medal, their fourth one in the Universiade fencing tournament.
</P>
<P>
The Russian team no longer had the good luck in the finals and lost
to Hungary 45-28, the greatest gap been ever seen in the finals since
the beginning of the fencing tournament at the on-going Universiade.
</P>
<P>
The Hungarian team entered the finals after beating Germany 45-38.
The title was their first fencing gold at this World University Games.
</P>
</TEXT>
