<HEADLINE> Fighting Escalated in Congo (B) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Fighting has escalated in Congo
with troops loyal to Congolese President Pascal Lissouba using
helicopters to bomb positions held by militiamen loyal to former
President Sassou Nguesso, according to Radio Cameroun today.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time that helicopters were deployed since the
two sides clashed on June 5 in Brazzaville, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said President Lissouba's forces fired rockets
before the raid. The rockets and the helicopters targeted a
stronghold of Sassou, Lissouba's predecessor and rival.
</P>
<P>
There was no immediate information from Brazzaville on the
casualties or damage.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, President Lissouba has agreed to send a delegation
to the Gabonese capital Libreville to restore negotiations with
the representatives of Sassou.
</P>
<P>
Gabonese President Omar Bongo will continue mediating in the
Congolese conflict. The United Nation has appraised Bongo for his
efforts to bring an end to the conflict. 
</P>
