<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Chinese
Communist Party Central Committee, has urged various localities to
wholeheartedly rely on workers in the drive to advance reforms,
opening-up and socialist construction into the next century.
</P>
<P>
Addressing to a conference at the Handan Iron and Steel Company
in north China's Hebei Province which focused on exchanging
experience in relying on workers, Hu said that at this important
historical moment of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics, we must unremittingly adhere to the policy of
relying on the working class, particularly during the ongoing
reforms of state enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Hu, also a member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central
Committee, called for various localities to adopt measures to
ensure that workers participate in and supervise the management of
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to the conference, Chinese vice-premier Wu Bangguo
said that the country should wholeheartedly rely on the workers
throughout the reforms and opening-up and socialist construction.
</P>
<P>
Wu noted that various localities should give full play to the
initiatives of the workers and protect their legitimate rights and
interests. 
