<HEADLINE> HK Airport Authority Awards More Catering Licenses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Airport
Authority (AA) today awarded two more commercial catering licenses
at Sky Mall, the retail complex inside the passenger terminal at
the new airport now under construction at Chek Lap Kok.
</P>
<P>
Under the 58-month licenses, three Asian food outlets will be
set up at the new airport, scheduled to open in April 1998 on an
outlying small island named Chek Lap Lok in the west of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Jumbo Mass Ltd., well known for its Southeast and South Asian
food, won a license to operate an outlet, while the other
licensee LSG Lufthansa Services Hong Kong Ltd. will open a
cafeteria and a snack bar.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, LSG won a license to operate two Western
food outlets at Hong Kong Sky Mall. The company runs 64 airport
restaurants around the world, including one at Kai Tak Airport in
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The two new licenses brought the number of food and beverage
outlets at Sky Mall to 25, offering a wider range of choices for
tens of millions of passengers who visit Hong Kong each year,
sources from AA said.  
</P>
