<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Launches Operation Against Illegal Immigrants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong has mounted a
blanket operation against illegal immigration and arrested 82
people, the Government Information Services reported today.
</P>
<P>
Among the arrested, 24 were suspected illegal immigrants, and
the others were caught for aiding or abetting overstay. The
operation was jointly launched by the Police, the Immigration
Department and the Labor Department.
</P>
<P>
A government spokesman reiterated today that there was no
question of any amnesty for illegal immigrants, who would be
repatriated.
</P>
<P>
"Our latest operation should drive home the point that there
will be no change to this policy. Anyone foolish enough to believe
otherwise is only cheating oneself," he said.
</P>
<P>
Apart from continuous checks throughout the city, police will
maintain a high state of vigilance both at the land and sea
borders, according to the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
During the 24-hour operation that ended on Wednesday morning,
the police stopped more than 7,000 persons, 144 vehicles and
nearly 500 vessels for identification checks. Immigration
investigators and labor inspectors visited thousands of
establishments to weed out illegal immigrants.
</P>
<P>
In Hong Kong, employers could be fined up to 350,000 HK
dollars (45,000 US dollars) and jailed for three years if they
employ illegal immigrants.  
</P>
</TEXT>
