<HEADLINE> News Analysis: Party Congress to Highlight Deng's Legacy (5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A series of major economic reform measures, similar to the
experimental steps in the reform of state businesses and the form
of public ownership, are expected to follow the convening of the
15th National Party Congress.
</P>
<P>
Various fields have never been subject to significant reforms
and, therefore, some doubts and difficulties are inevitable.
Disputes on issues such as the use of foreign funds, private
businesses, and the appropriate proportion for the state sector in
the entire national economy, etc.
</P>
<P>
Hence, various contradictions and doubts must be solved and a
common understanding must be reached within the Party concerning
Deng's theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Yang Chungui, vice-president of the Party School, said: "the
most pressing matter rests with quelling any type of disturbances,
avoid senseless abstract debates and silly manoeuvring."
</P>
<P>
China faces both heated challenge and precious opportunities
both at home and abroad at the turn of the century. "China has all
the favorable conditions necessary for accelerated development,"
Yang said.
</P>
<P>
Hu Angang, a research fellow with the Chinese Academy of
Sciences, agreed that China's predicted economic upsurge will
exert great influence across the world.
</P>
<P>
"However, it will not be an easy job," Hu said, adding that "We
should actively respond to all aspects of major challenges. The
only wise and historical option is to proceed in accordance with
China's unique situation, continue to emancipate our minds and
squarely meet all challenges."  
</P>
</TEXT>
