<HEADLINE> Shanghai Leads Nation in Mobile Phone Users </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai in east China leads
the nation with 500,000 mobile phone subscribers.
</P>
<P>
The figure represents dramatic growth on the city's 300,000
mobile phone users in 1996 and 100,000 in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has invested more than three billion yuan in the
development of its local mobile communications sector since 1992
when it had a mere 10,000 mobile phone users.
</P>
<P>
The handling capacity of the local mobile communications
network is expected to increase to one million lines from present
800,000 lines by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
Local mobile communications networks are now linked to other
similar networks nationwide in 31 provinces, regions and
municipalities. The local "139" network currently offers roaming
services linking 12 overseas countries and regions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
