<HEADLINE> Five Nepalese Killed by Lightning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Five people were killed and
another injured Monday by lightning in Ramechhap district of
central Nepal, the official RSS news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
One women was killed while working in the fields.
</P>
<P>
Her 15-year-old son was injured by the lightning, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
Lightning death is very common in Nepal during the monsoon
season, which runs from June to September.  
