<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ninth PACAP Finance Conference Closes in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The Ninth PACAP finance
conference came to a close today in Shanghai, China's largest
financial and industrial center.
</P>
<P>
Participants to the conference spoke highly of China's
achievements in financial reform, but also called for a faster
pace in opening China's financial market under the prerequisite of
maintaining stability and standard operations.
</P>
<P>
The four-day conference was jointly sponsored by the Chinese
Education Association for International Exchange and the PACAP
Research Center at University of Rhode Island.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 600 financial experts and industrialists from 14 Asian
and Pacific countries attended the meeting, during which experts
participated in extensive discussions about the development of
financial and capital markets in China and other Asian and Pacific
countries.
</P>
<P>
More than 50 seminars and panel discussions were held during
the conference.
</P>
<P>
The first PACAP conference was held in 1989.  
</P>
</TEXT>
