<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Bank employees in India's
capital New Delhi today started a two-day strike paralyzing all
the banking activities in the city.
</P>
<P>
The strike was called by the United Forum of Bank Unions (UFBU)
to force the government among other things to withdraw an
"illegal" clause in pension regulations denying the benefit to
employees for "participation in strike".
</P>
<P>
