today as nearly 1.5 million employees of the country's banks
stopped work on the first day of the two-day strike in support of
their demands, Press Trust of India (PTI) said.
</P>
<P>
The striking employees took out processions and held
demonstrations in various parts of the country. In a statement in
Calcutta, the UFBU said that the strike was "complete, total and
peaceful".  
