<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Reduces Overseas Telephone Call Charge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will cut the overseas
telephone call charge by 10 percent and the new rate will be
effective on September 1, according to a press release issued here
today by the Bangladesh Telegraph and Telephone Board (BTTB).
</P>
<P>
The schedules for peak and off-peak hours will also be changed,
the release said. The morning schedule for peak hours will be from
8:30 a.m. to 11 p.m. (local time) while the off-peak hours will be
from 11 p.m. to 8:30 a.m. in the next morning, it added.
</P>
<P>
The 25 percent reduce in call charges on weekend days and
government holidays will remain unchanged, the press release said.
</P>
<P>
As an example, per minute telephone call charge from Bangladesh
to the United States will be 72 taka (about 1.61 U.S. dollars)
instead of 80 taka (about 1.8 dollars).
</P>
<P>
On weekend days and official holidays the per minute call
charge to the U.S. will be 54 taka (about 1.21 dollars).
</P>
<P>
While reducing the overseas call charge, BTTB has also
increased the number of international telecommunication circuits,
said the release.  
</P>
</TEXT>
