<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market today lost 134.41 points to
close at 3,963.15 as against Wednesday's close of 4,097.56.
</P>
<P>
The national index fell by 54.93 points to 1,732.78 from the
previous close of 1,787.71.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and U.S. dollar index were quoted down at 389.05
and 178.14 as compared with the previous close of 401.68 and
183.93 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Speculators suffered yet another sharp setback, bringing the
sensitive index down by over 134 points to below the 4,000 mark on
the BSE market today in the wake of heavy off-loading by foreign
institutional investors and bull operators.
</P>
<P>
There was all-round selling by players on the market in the
absence of any support even from domestic financial institutions.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said that market operators were worried over the
continued depreciation of the rupee against the dollar in spite of
heavy intervention by the Reserve Bank of India in support of the
rupee. 
</P>
