<HEADLINE> Zhengzhou Airport Opens to Traffic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The airport in Zhengzhou,
capital of central China's Henan Province opened to traffic today
and is expected to be a major factor helping to promote local
economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The Xinzheng Airport, built at a cost of about 1.2 billion
yuan, is located 34 kilometers from downtown Zhengzhou. The
facility, which was constructed in accordance with the nation's
highest 4E standards, has a 3,400-meter runway and taxiways
capable of servicing Boeing 747-400, the world's largest
long-range passenger aircraft.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the airport, which covers more than 400 ha.,
commenced three years ago, and the facility has been listed as one
of nation's major air hubs.
</P>
<P>
The airport will offer regularly scheduled flights to Hong Kong
and Singapore, and will add flights to more cities in Southeast
Asia, Europe and the United States in the near future.
</P>
<P>
The old and poorly equipped airport was used for both civil and
military purpose. 
</P>
</TEXT>
