still remains in a deficit position.
</P>
<P>
Statistics Canada reported today that foreign visitors injected
2.2 billion U.S. dollars into the Canadian economy in the second
quarter, almost unchanged from the previous quarter.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Canadians travelers spent 2.7 billion dollars
abroad, down 1.4 percent from the first quarter.
</P>
<P>
As a result, Canada's international travel account deficit
dropped 8.5 percent, from 540 million dollars in the first quarter
to 500 million dollars in the second.
</P>
<P>
The deficit peaked at 1.4 billion dollars during the last
quarter of 1991. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
