<HEADLINE> Two Greek Jet Fighters Crash Into Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Two Greek Air Force A-7 jet
fighters crashed late Wednesday night into the sea near Kalamata
in southwestern Greece, after colliding in the air during a
training exercise.
</P>
<P>
Greek Air Force General Staff announced here today that before
the crash, the two pilots ejected safely and were later rescued
from the sea by Greek Navy.
</P>
<P>
A pilot on a Mirage-2000 of the Greek Air force died in another
accident occurred on July 28 when the fighter plane crashed into
the Aegean Sea while conducting a routine training flight. 
</P>
