<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Indian Defense Minister
Mulayam Singh Yadav said today that India would begin serial
production of short-range surface-to-air missile "Trishul" next
year.
</P>
<P>
The developmental trials of medium-range surface-to-air missile
"Akash" with multiple target handling capability were continuing
and the missile would be inducted into the armed forces after user
trials were completed, he said.
</P>
<P>
India is also making efforts to test-fly its sophisticated
light combat aircraft in December, the minister said.  
