<HEADLINE> China to Hold International Educational Equipment Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The Fourth China International
Educational Instrument and Equipment Exhibition is expected to be
held here from September 3-6, sources from the State Education
Commission (SEC) announced today.
</P>
<P>
The four-day event is designed to help Chinese schools and
related organizations learn more about development of advanced
educational aids in the world, a SEC official said at a SEC press
conference here today.
</P>
<P>
"At the same time, the exhibition will provide a chance for
production cooperation and trade exchanges between Chinese
manufacturers and foreign businessmen," the official said.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 60 exhibitors from a number of countries and regions
such as the United States, Britain and Germany will attend the
show and display their hi-tech materials and equipment for basic
education and technological research, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 150 domestic educational instrument dealers will
show more than 1,000 varieties of their latest products including
computers, educational software, multi-media and language lab
equipment, analysis instruments, and equipment for vocational
education, special education, and pre-school education.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Chinese and foreign experts will host a series of
seminars and academic exchange programs on the theme of
"Educational Technique and Equipment for Education Promotion."
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is sponsored by the China Educational Instrument
and Equipment Corporation under the SEC. 
</P>
</TEXT>
