<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cultural Exchanges Across Taiwan Straits Expanding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Cultural exchanges across Taiwan
Straits kept growing in the first half of the year.
</P>
<P>
There were 108 groups with some 1,300 people altogether from
the two sides that visited each other during the period, staging
performances, giving exhibitions, or holding seminars and
symposiums.
</P>
<P>
307 people on Taiwan visited the mainland, an increase of 73
percent from the same period of the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Troupes of performers accounted for a large proportion of the
exchanges, which were warmly received by people from both sides.
</P>
<P>
Cultural training is another major form of exchange. A teaching
program sponsored by the Beijing Drama School and a Taiwan art
school has sent 74 artists from Beijing to Taiwan to teach Peking
Opera in the past four years. It is expected to be extended to
other traditional Chinese folk arts.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
