announced a total of 143 key projects here in Beijing today
for overseas cooperation partners.
</P>
<P>
The Anhui '97 Foreign Economic Cooperation Fair, which opened
in the Beijing International Trade Center, attracted over 2,000
people from more than 400 Chinese and foreign companies.
</P>
<P>
Seminars on energy, communications and other sectors will be
held during the three-day fair.
</P>
<P>
Wu Yi, Chinese minister of foreign trade and economic
cooperation, sent a letter of congratulations to the fair.
</P>
<P>
Wu described the fair as "an important step" taken by Anhui to
fuel the development of the province through opening up to the
outside world.
</P>
<P>
Anhui Governor Hui Liangyu said geographical advantages and
preferential policies provide favorable conditions for the
province to speed up development and boost all-round opening-up to
the outside world.
</P>
<P>
