<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Vows More Reforms and Wider Opening in Commerce Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The internal trade sector is
vowing to deepen its reforms and opening so as to better align its
operations with the socialist market economy, a high-ranking
commerce official said here today.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, Chen Bangzhu, minister of Internal
Trade, said that as internal trade is an important sector in the
national economy closely related to people's life and production,
issues related to the reforms, opening-up, development and
stability of the sector must be carefully handled.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Internal Trade was founded in 1993 when the
government made moves to streamline, incorporating the three
ministries previously in charge of commerce, grain and material
distribution.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that since China needs to feed a population
of 1.2 billion and more, the prosperity and stability of the grain
market basically guarantee a stable national economy.
</P>
<P>
"One important task is to take advantage of the present stable
market condition to deepen the reform of the grain distribution
sector," he said.
</P>
<P>
In the coming years, a grain market system will be formed to
bring about the opening-up in a unified way and encourage fair
competition.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, measures will also be taken to establish a market
regulation system for more effective supervision.
</P>
<P>
Also under the plan, the policy-oriented grain distribution
will be separated from purely commercial practices and more
State-owned grain stores will be allowed to operate under market
competition, the minister observed.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
