<DOCNO> XIE19970828.0134 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Vows More Reform and Open-up in Commerce Sector (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With ample supply and stable prices, the total retail sales of
consumer goods reached 2,461.4 billion yuan (about 296.5 billion US
dollars) in 1996, more than triple the 1991 figure.
</P>
<P>
To ensure a continuously prosperous market which will
constantly meet the growing demand, the market must be vigorously
expanded by increasing the cooperation between the industrial and
commercial departments, Chen said.
</P>
<P>
Rural income has grown faster than urban income in recent
years, however, the rural market has become sluggish and special
focus should be placed on reviving it, the minister noted.
</P>
<P>
To this end, measures should be taken to increase the supply of
marketable goods, to set up more chain stores and distribution
centers and to establish more commodity service centers in rural
areas, he urged.
</P>
<P>
Regarding the development of new distribution forms, Chen said,
the next step is to expand the operation scale and standardize
chain stores and distribution centers. The proposed solutions
include adding more outlets and commodities and speeding up the
formulation of laws and legislations.
</P>
<P>
"In the process, we should try to borrow from advanced foreign
experience, continue to absorb foreign funds, technology and
personnel in a cautious manner, and set up more Sino-overseas
joint ventures," he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
In reviewing the achievements of the reform and opening drive,
the minister said that the majority of the commodities previously
under state review are now distributed throughout the market, with
the price of 90 to 95 percent of the commodities being set freely.
</P>
<P>
While in the past, department stores dominated the market,
supermarkets, convenience stores, boutiques and warehouse stores
are now on the scene.
</P>
<P>
In the opening-up drive, the central government has approved 17
large Sino-overseas department store projects and granted
the right to handle imports and exports to 206 state-owned
distribution enterprises. In addition, about 7,000 enterprises
involving overseas investment have been set up.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
