<HEADLINE> China Calls for Ceasefire in Congo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- China today appealed to the
conflicting parties in the Republic of Congo to agree to a
ceasefire and bring peace and stability back to the country.
</P>
<P>
Asked at a weekly press conference to comment on the two-month
armed conflicts in the Congo, which have recently escalated,
Foreign Ministry spokesman Tang Guoqiang said that the Chinese
government is greatly concerned about the latest developments in
the Congo.
</P>
<P>
"We appealed to the conflicting parties in the Congo to proceed
from the interest of the country and the wish of its people, and
to establish a ceasefire, eliminate differences through dialogue,
reach reconciliation, and finally bring back peace and stability
to the Congo," Tang said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman added that China appreciates and supports the
"positive efforts" of the international community, Gabon's
President El Hadj Omar Bongo in particular, to restore peace in
the Congo.  
