<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The embassy of the Democratic
People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) in Cairo has accused its two
senior diplomats who defected to the U.S. last weekend as
"criminals" and demanded their repatriation.
</P>
<P>
A press statement faxed to Xinhua this morning said DPRK
Ambassador to Egypt Jang Sun Gil and his elder brother Jang Sung
Ho, DPRK's trade representative in Paris, had been ordered home
before their defections.
</P>
<P>
"It is very clear and correct that Jang Sung Gil and his
brother had been dismissed from their posts early in last July and
had been ordered to return home for judicial investigation for
embezzlement of a large sum of public funds and degeneration," the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
"We demand the United States hand over Jang Sung Gil and his
brother to DPR of Korea in accordance with the international law
on extradition," the statement, in English, said. 
