<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets Laotian Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng said
here today that the Chinese government attaches great importance
to developing a neighborly friendship with Laos, and is ready to
work together with Laos to bring closer Sino-Laotian ties into the
next century.
</P>
<P>
Li made the remark when meeting with visiting Laotian Foreign
Minister Somsavat Lengsavad, who is here on an official goodwill
visit to China.
</P>
<P>
Li welcomed Somsavat and asked him to convey General Secretary
of the Central Committee of the Chinese Communist Party Jiang
Zemin's and his regards to Khamtay Siphandone, president of the
Central Committee of the Lao People's Revolutionary Party and
Laotian Prime Minister.
</P>
<P>
Noting that he is satisfied with the smooth development of
relations between the two parties and the two countries, Li said
that Sino-Lao traditional friendship has a long history and the
two peoples have lived in harmony, adding that the two countries
successfully settled border issues long ago.
</P>
<P>
During Somsavat's visit, the two sides signed a supplementary
protocol to a border treaty between China and Laos, which will
standardize the management of the border between the two
countries, Li added.
</P>
<P>
Conveying Khamtay Siphandone's greetings to Jiang and Li,
Somsavat said that there are no sensitive issues existing between
Laos and China, and the Laotian party, government and people are
pleasant at the the smooth development of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Laotian side is willing to join hands with the
Chinese in building a bilateral good-neighborly friendship for the
next century.
</P>
<P>
Somsavat and his party left here this afternoon for Xi'an,
capital of northwest China's Shaanxi Province to continue their
China trip. 
</P>
