<HEADLINE> Philippines to Formulate Long-term Development Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
today ordered the formulation of a national development plan for
the 21st century which includes the country's long-term vision,
policy framework, targets and strategies.
</P>
<P>
In a circular to the National Economic Development Authority
(NEDA), Ramos called for the preparation of a success plan for the
period from 1990 to 2004 and a long-term plan up to the year 2025.
</P>
<P>
Ramos said a long-term development blueprint is necessary "to
ensure economic stability and consistency of government policies
and programs" and sustain the gains the Philippines has achieved
in the past five years.
</P>
<P>
The president asked the NEDA as the central planning agency of
the government to coordinate with other agencies of the executive
branch, the legislative branch and private sector in preparing the
development plan.
</P>
<P>
The plan shall contain the following basic elements --
development goals and objectives; strategy and policy framework to
attain such goals and objectives; and key measurable targets
supportive of broader development objectives, according to the
president.
</P>
<P>
Ramos said all sectors of society, public or private, shall be
consulted to the fullest to obtain their opinions and positions on
related matters.  
</P>
</TEXT>
