<HEADLINE> HK to Launch Man-Made Reef Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region government will launch a project worth 100
million HK dollars (12.82 million US dollars) for the growth and
diversification of marine life in the next four years.
</P>
<P>
A government official told provisional legislators on Wednesday
that 150 man-made reefs would be dropped into the sea to provide
food and protection for fish. The first reef would be put in place
by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
The Provisional Legislative Council yesterday unanimously
supported independent Lo Suk-ching's motion urging the government
to formulate a long-term policy for the dwindling agricultural and
fishery industries.
</P>
<P>
Lo said the industries' future would rely on high technology,
requiring direct government financial support.  
