<HEADLINE> HK Food Poisoning Cases Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The number of food poisoning
cases in Hong Kong doubled in the first six months of this year,
compared with the same period last year, sources from the local
health department said.
</P>
<P>
The local health department received a total of 151 reports of
food poisoning, affecting 820 people between January and June this
year.
</P>
<P>
Bacteria was the major cause, accounting for 82 percent of the
cases, mostly as a result of under-cooking and contamination
during processing.
</P>
<P>
But a spokesman said the overall trend was similar to the
corresponding period in 1996 and within acceptable levels.
</P>
<P>
Last year there were a total of 314 food poisoning cases in
Hong Kong, affecting 1,820 people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
