<HEADLINE> CPC National Congress Welcomes Chinese, Foreign Correspondents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese and foreign
correspondents are welcome to cover the upcoming 15th National
Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC), sources close to
the congress have announced.
</P>
<P>
The deadline for accepting applications is September 8.
</P>
<P>
Journalists from the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR), Macao and Taiwan are asked to present their applications
to the Hong Kong or Macao branches of the Xinhua News Agency or
the Taiwan Affairs Office of the State Council.
</P>
<P>
They also should include letters of reference from their press
organizations or correspondent certifications when submitting
applications.
</P>
<P>
Foreign correspondents are required to submit their
applications to Chinese embassies and consulates abroad, the
Commissioner's Office of the Foreign Ministry in Hong Kong or the
Visa Office of the Foreign Ministry in Macao, or the Information
Department of the Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
During the congress, a press center will be set up in the Media
Hotel in Beijing to help arrange coverage of activities related to
the congress, interviews for Chinese and foreign reporters and
also press conferences.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the press center will provide information and
telecommunications services for reporters.
</P>
<P>
The center's consultation telephone and fax numbers for Hong
Kong, Macao and Taiwan reporters are 68521600 (Tel) and 68521800
(Fax), those for foreign reporters are 68524100 (Tel) and 68524400
(Fax). 
</P>
</TEXT>
