<HEADLINE> Share Prices Decline Sharply on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined sharply
on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index plunged by 69.34 points to close at 1,846.62 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased to 286.35 million units,
valued at 580.31 million Singapore dollars (about 386.87 million
US dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 377 to 27, while 202
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Hotung was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 27.15 million units. It was followed by MBf Capital
which had 11.56 million shares traded. Redapac was next with 11.34
million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Land clWarrant98 and Shangri-La shared the top
spot on the short list of the gainers of the day as each of them
rose by 60 cents to finish at 0.45 US dollar and 4.02 Singapore
dollars respectively. SGM and Yeo Hss gained 50 cents each to end
at 1.08 Hong Kong dollars and 5.05 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign was
the biggest loser as it declined by 2.4 dollars to close at 21.6
Singapore dollars. GE Life fell by 1.9 dollars to finish at 15.5
Singapore dollars, while Samanda Holdings and the United Overseas
Bank (UOB) Foreign ended 1.4 dollars lower at 5.6 and 12.1
Singapore dollars respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
