<HEADLINE> 18 Nepalese Injured by Mad Dog </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 28 (Xinhua) -- A mad dog injured 18 people
Wednesday in Syangja district of western Nepal, prompting the
authorities to kill some more stray dogs, the official RSS news
agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The injured are now undergoing treatment at the local hospital.
</P>
<P>
As an immediate measure to control further bites and the rising
population of the stray dogs, the authorities poisoned another 45
such dogs Wednesday, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
The authorities have launched a drive to kill the stray dogs
after they caused a terror in the area and began targeting
unsuspecting children, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
As stray dogs roam the cities and villages throughout Nepal,
cases of dog bites and death of rabies are very common.
</P>
<P>
The capital city of Kathmandu has also launched a drive to kill
the stray dogs in preparation for the Visit Nepal Year '98.
</P>
</TEXT>
