<HEADLINE> CPPCC Vice-Chairman Meets Japanese Youth Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Wu Xueqian, vice-chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), met here today with a number of members of a
youth delegation from Kyushu of Japan.
</P>
<P>
The "Youth Network Wing" delegation is led by Governor
Matsukata Suketaka of Miyazaki Prefecture.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is the 22nd of its kind from Kyushu since 1974.
Over 10,000 Japanese young people have joined such delegations to
visit China by planes or ships.
</P>
<P>
He Guangwei, director of China's National Tourism
Administration, attended the meeting. 
</P>
