<HEADLINE> China, Russia Sign Protocol in Diamond, Noble Metals Processing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Geology and
Mineral Resources today signed a protocol with Russia's Committee
of State Noble Metals to cooperate in exploration and processing
of diamonds and noble metals.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Minister of Geology and Mineral Resources Song Ruixiang
and the Russian committee's Chairman German Kuznetsov inked the
agreement.
</P>
<P>
According to the five-year protocol, the two countries will
cooperate on exploration, surveying, mining, ore dressing and
processing of diamond and noble metals, as well as on technology
transfer and establishing joint ventures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
