<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPC Solicits Non-Communists' Opinions on Party Congress Report (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At present, Jiang said, the reform and construction in China
have entered a new, crucial phase, which requires China to pool
efforts in various aspects and work together toward common goals.
</P>
<P>
This calls for the continued strengthening and development of
patriotic united front, which is essential to form the broadest
alliance consisting of all socialist laborers and all patriots who
support socialism and the reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Democratic parties and figures without party affiliations are
an important force of the united patriotic front during the new
period, he said. The CPC will unswervingly uphold the policy of
"long-term coexistence and mutual supervision, and treating with
each other honestly and sharing trials and tribulations," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang noted that the CPC will give support to democratic
parties and non-Party figures in their participation and
discussion of government and political affairs. The CPC also will
respect and give full play to their active roles in political
consultations, democratic supervision, and management of state and
social affairs.
</P>
<P>
The CPC will further develop a close cooperative relationship
with democratic parties and non-Party figures, in which all sides
will treat each other on an equal footing, unite and move forward
together, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, democratic parties and non-Party figures should
consciously accept the leadership of the CPC and, in accordance
with their own characteristics and advantages, carry out their
work actively and contribute still more to the great cause of
advancing socialism with Chinese characteristics as well as the
great cause of reunification of the motherland, Jiang said.
</P>
</TEXT>
