<HEADLINE> CPC Solicits Non-Communists' Opinions on Party Congress Report (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang said the 15th CPC National Congress will work out a
strategic, programmatic plan for China's cross-century reform,
opening-up and modernization construction.
</P>
<P>
It will be a congress with great historical significance for
the CPC, as well as for the country and the people, Jiang
said. The whole nation has been looking forward to the congress,
which also has drawn great attention of the international
community.
</P>
<P>
To make the congress a success is not only a lofty
responsibility of the CPC, according to Jiang, but also requires
tremendous support from various non-Communist Parties, the
All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce, figures with no
party affiliation, and all the people as a whole.
</P>
<P>
China should unite in all aspects of the work to greet the
successful convening of the 15th CPC National Congress, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of various non-Communist Parties and the All-China
Federation of Industry and Commerce, as well as representatives of
figures without party affiliation have read and discussed the
draft report of the 15th CPC National Congress (the draft report
for solicitation of opinions), at the invitation of the United
Front Work Department of the CPC Central Committee as authorized
by the CPC Central Committee.
