<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading French newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- French researchers Dominique Goux and Eric Maurin said in a
study published today that the wealth of parents is no longer the
source of success for schoolchildren.
</P>
<P>
They said despite the openness of public schools to all
children, inequality in education among schoolchildren continue to
exist. Inequality in cultural background and the capability of
parents to help their children pass the exams and choose their
orientation are the main reasons for the persistence of inequality
among children in education.
</P>
<P>
-- According to American doctor Philip Reilly, the author of
"History of Involuntary Sterilization in the United States", more
than 60,000 Americans were forcibly sterilized from 1907 to 1960
under a policy to eliminate the "undesirable", including mentally
handicapped, alcoholics, violent criminals, sexual delinquents or
simply members of ethnic groups considered a threat to the
supremacy of the white race.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- German Chancellor Helmut Kohl today will meet French Prime
Minister Lionel Jospin who will be on his first visit to Germany
since taking office.
</P>
<P>
Kohl and Jospin will focus their talks on Europan issues,
including the Franco-German summit in Weimar on September 19 and
the European job conference to be held in Luxembourg in November.
</P>
<P>
-- French President Jacques Chirac told about 200 French
ambassadors stationed abroad on Wednesday that France, which is
occupying "an eminent but fragile position" in the world, does not
"have the right to err" in the face of the challenge from
globalization.
</P>
<P>
He said that France cannot achieve its economic and social
progress without an adaptation to the globalization, and that
Europe should become a major pole of power in the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
