<DOCNO> XIE19970828.0180 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Preserving Tibetan Culture (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In 1986, the Tibetan government established a cultural heritage
preservation group that, in the following decade, traveled
every corner of Tibet gathering a large amount of data on the
region's art and culture.
</P>
<P>
"I dare say, we've not neglected a single piece of these
treasured items," Dandzim Cering says.
</P>
<P>
An urgent task is to publish all the information. Ten books are
scheduled for publication before the year 2000, covering Tibetan
drama, folk dance, folk music, musical instruments, and other
topics. The book Tibetan Drama, alone, has 860,000 characters and
over 300 pictures.
</P>
<P>
Tibet now has over 160 groups of performers who are on tour
constantly. "And all modern art forms have influenced works and
artists here, making Tibet a much more vigorous area," says an
official in the Culture Department of Tibet.
</P>
<P>
However, Tibetan artists are not satisfied with their findings
and are trying to develop them further for modern society. Dandzim
Cering and his colleagues have collected and collated materials on a
dance called 'Xianwu', which is said to have a history of more
than 3000 years. When it was put on stage in Beijing and Hong Kong
in 1994 in its original form, 'Xianwu' became a hit.
</P>
<P>
"We've revived this `fossilized' dance," Dandzim Cering says,
smiling. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970828.0181 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Economy Grows 5.9 Pct in First Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' economy slowed
down to 5.9 percent in the first half of this year compared with
7.5 percent recorded in the same period last year, statistics
released today by the National Economic Development Authority
showed.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Philippines' Gross Domestic Product (GDP) -- the
total value of goods produced in a country -- grew by 5.3 percent,
also slower than last year's 5.6 percent, according to the
statistics.
</P>
<P>
The economic growth in the first six months of the year was
helped by an increase of 12.2 percent in investments and a solid
push coming from the domestic production sectors led by
construction, manufacturing and financial service.
</P>
<P>
The services sector outpaced other sectors, registering a
strong growth of 6.3 percent and contributing 51.1 percent to the
total growth of the domestic production.
</P>
<P>
Industry followed with a 5.4 percent rise and a share of 35.3
percent to the GDP. The combined agriculture, fishery and forestry
sector completed the picture with a 3.4 percent growth rate and a
13.6 percent share to the GDP.
</P>
<P>
Merchandise exports went up by 22 percent in the first six
months. However, the poor performance of the non-merchandise
exports, which showed negative growth, plunged the total exports
in the first half of this year to 7.1 percent compared with last
year's 25.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
To achieve the full-year economic growth of seven percent
planned by the government, an 8.1 percent growth is required for
the second half of the year.
</P>
<P>
However, economic analysts doubted the projection, recommending
that the government reassess the growth prospects for the whole
year, especially after the currency of peso has been devaluating
since early July.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
