<HEADLINE> Chinese President Ignites Torch for National Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
ignited the main torch here on Thursday to start the torch relay
throughout the country for the coming Eighth National Games.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also general secretary of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC), set the flame in the quadripod to
the torch and waved it to the enthusiastic crowds at the Tiananmen
Square.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese President then passed the torch to Wu Shaozu,
minister of the Chinese State Physical Culture and Sports
Commission and also chairman of the National Games Organizing
Committee.
</P>
<P>
Also attending the ceremony entitled "Running Towards the New
Century" were Hu Jintao, member of the Standing Committee of the
Political Bureau of CPC Central Committee, and other Chinese
leaders and top sports officials.
</P>
<P>
The flame of the quadripod placed at the eastern gate of the
Great Hall of People, was ignited first by two flames from
Shanghai, where the games will be staged from October 12-24, and
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
Minister Wu then handed the main torch to the first bearer Xu
Haifeng, who won China's first Olympic gold medal at the Los
Angeles Games in 1984.
</P>
<P>
The Olympic champion and other torch bearers from 32 provinces,
autonomous regions, municipalities and Hong Kong SAR ran the first
leg of the relay at the square.
</P>
<P>
The torch will arrive in Shanghai before the opening ceremony
of the National Games and the games' flame will be ignited on
October 12.
</P>
<P>
More than 7,500 athletes will participate in the quadrennial
games which feature 28 sports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
