<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mongolia to Provide Loans for Poor College Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Mongolia's State Educational
Fund will provide loans for the poor college students as from
September 1 to help them complete their studies, local reports
said today.
</P>
<P>
The students living under the poverty line can apply for the
loans, which have no interest when the students are at the college.
</P>
<P>
The students granted by the loans are required to pay off
within six years with an interest which is about one percentage
point higher than the inflation rate.
</P>
<P>
Mongolia's official statistics show that by the end of 1996,
the number of poor families in the country had reached 103,500, an
increase of 23,100 over the previous year and accounting for 20
percent of the total population. 
</P>
</TEXT>
