<HEADLINE> Good Company Results Lead Australian Stock Market Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Good company profit
announcements saw the Australian share market close higher in
light trading today, but the increase was tempered by offshore
market falls, brokers said.
</P>
<P>
The All Ordinaries index rose 4.8 points to 2631.3, with rises
in industrial stocks, but resources generally fell marginally.
</P>
<P>
"There have been some good results and we're entitled to start
on our upturn today," Stuart Smith from Henderson Charlton Jones
said.
</P>
<P>
"However I think we have had one eye on the Hang Seng which is
down 2.4 percent and I think that has held us back or we might
have maintained a bigger rise," he said.
</P>
<P>
Among the major company results today, Brambles recorded a 13
percent rise in net profit to 179 million U.S. dollars, a result
which pushed its share price up five cents to 27.75 Australian
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Shares in Computershare rose more than 7 cents to 14.50
Australian dollars after an improved net profit result, while
casino company Crown bounced back 6 cents to 1.70 Australian
dollars after recent falls relating to a 53 million U.S. dollar
post-abnormal loss announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
News Corp. shares rose 5 cents to 6.03 Australian dollars while
its preferred stock climbed three cents to 5.13 Australian
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The All Industrials index rose 11.1 points to 4235.4 but the
All Resources fell 0.6 points to 1380.4.
</P>
<P>
Miner RGC rose six cents to 3.81 Australian dollars despite
reporting a 57 million U.S. dollar net loss, Pasminco shares
dropped 9.1 cents to 2.549 Australian dollars, and BHP, the
country's biggest company, closed 4 cents better at 17.25
Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Gold prices rose, with bullion closing at 325.55 U.S. dollars
compared to Wednesday's close of 325.30 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
National turnover for the day was a light 288.44 million shares
at a value of 688.19 million Australian dollars (509.70 million
U.S. dollars), with falls outnumbering rises by 566 to 503.
</P>
</TEXT>
