<HEADLINE> United States Trounces Cuba, Puerto Rico Beats Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The United States trounced
Cuba 100-88 in the second round of the basketball tournament of
the Americas on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Travis Williams and Mike McDonald each scored 17 points for the
United States, who led the first half 59-47. Cuba, who had strong
back court line-ups but was weaker at forwards, had no effective
inside weapon against the American's strong defence.
</P>
<P>
Lazaro Borrel hit a game high 24 points for Cuba, but failed to
change the inevitable results.
</P>
<P>
In other matches, Puerto Rico shook off the embarrassment of
three straight loses in the first round to beat Argentina 88-83,
thanks to Jose Ortiz's match-high 25 points.
</P>
<P>
Brazil made a significant stride by victory over Venezuela
88-79, though Victor Diaz tallying a game high 36 points for
Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
In the last game on Wednesday, Canada beat hosts Uruguay with
Rowan Barret scoring 15 points for the winner.
</P>
<P>
the top four finishers of the tournament will qualify for the
1998 world championships finals in Greece. The United States
qualifies automatically as reigning champion. 
</P>
