<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Olympic Champions Receive IOC Awards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- China's Atlanta Olympic
champions received the top honors issued by the International
Olympic Committee (IOC) here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
At its congress of the Chinese Olympic Committee (COC), Deng
Yaping, women's table tennis champion, and Xiong Ni, men's diving
winner at the 26th Olympics one year ago, received the "IOC
Souvenir Awards" on behalf of the Chinese Olympic champions.
</P>
<P>
He Zhenliang, China's IOC member, presented the awards to the
Chinese gold medalists.
</P>
<P>
Wei Jizhong, COC secretary general who was elected COC
vice-president at the congress today, received the "1996 IOC
Centennial Olympics Award".
</P>
<P>
The COC also issued the "1997 IOC Mass Sports Award" to Liu Ji,
vice-minister of the Chinese State Physical Culture and Sports
Commission.
</P>
<P>
Tu Mingde, COC deputy secretary general, was elected COC
secretary general to replace Wei Jizhong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
