<HEADLINE> ADB to Extend Technical Assistance to Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
will provide a technical assistance grant of 850,000 U.S. dollars
to Indonesia to help strengthen the capacity of its national
agencies to promote private sector participation in urban
development.
</P>
<P>
In a press statement, the ADB said that efforts by the private
sector to participate in urban development will relieve the
pressure on public funds, reduce the backlog of infrastructure
investment and increase the efficiency of local service delivery.
</P>
<P>
The ADB grant will be used to train government officials in
project biddings, bid evaluation and negotiations with the private
sector on urban development, it said.  
</P>
