<HEADLINE> Hong Kong-Funded Brewery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, August 28 (Xinhua) -- A Hong Kong-funded brewery
will be built in Changchun, capital of northeast China's Jilin
Province.
</P>
<P>
The brewery, to be constructed at a cost of 245 million yuan,
will be jointly funded by the Changchun Brewery Co. and the New
China- Hong Kong Brewery Company. The Hong Kong company will
provide 60 percent of funding for the joint venture.
</P>
<P>
The brewery complex, which will cover 150,000 sq.m., will have
an annual beer production capacity of 100,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture is expected to revitalize the 45-year-old
Changchun Brewery Company which halted production two years
ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
