<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shangdong Reemployment Effort </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Shandong province in east China
has recently introduced a program to find jobs for half of its
600,000 unemployed people by the end of this year, according to
local officials.
</P>
<P>
Jobless people are being encouraged to form "household service
companies" and other types of businesses to reclaim wasteland or
work for township, private and foreign-funded enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government does not allow any enterprise to
simultaneously fire two members from a family. Enterprises should
help families with several jobless people find jobs as quickly as
possible.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises are also asked to hire unemployed workers at a rate
of no less than 20 percent when recruiting people. The rate for
new enterprises is no less than 30 percent.
</P>
<P>
Shandong has set a reemployment rate target of over 60 percent
for developed areas by the end of the year, with a 50 percent rate
for other areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
