<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Agricultural Development Policies Urged in SADC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Member states of the
South African Development Community (SADC) have been urged to
develop policies to stimulate and sustain agricultural
production.
</P>
<P>
This was suggested by Tanzanian Deputy Minister for
Agriculture Njelu Kasaka when he opened a three-day workshop on
experiences and lessons on linkage project involving researchers
and farmers organizations which started here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
It is regarded as part of the efforts to meet the food
requirements and improve living standards of the people in SADC
member countries.
</P>
<P>
To achieve the objective, Kasaka said, the countries should
ensure that food production growth exceed population growth which
is currently three percent in most countries in the region.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the need for the countries to direct their efforts
to small scale farmers who are the majority producers but
operating in quite complex systems. 
</P>
</TEXT>
