<HEADLINE> E. African States to Tighten Cooperation Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The permanent tripartite
commission for the East African Cooperation (EAC) will meet today
in Arusha, northern Tanzania to review progress made in
strengthening the regional cooperation since its last meeting in
April.
</P>
<P>
A news dispatch from Arusha said that the commission, which is
the highest decision-making body made up of ministers from Kenya,
Tanzania and Uganda, is expected to recommend upgrading the
cooperation into a treaty.
</P>
<P>
Another area to be considered by the commission will be the
establishment of a single market and investment in the three
partner countries.
</P>
<P>
Criteria for the expansion of the membership of the EAC will
be discussed at the meeting as Rwanda has made a formal
application to join the regional body.
</P>
<P>
Agricultural and livestock development, legal and judicial
cooperation, security and defense, trade, investment and tourism,
transport and communications, energy and meteorology will also be
touched in the meeting.  
</P>
