<HEADLINE> Japanese Released by Kidnappers in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 28 (Xinhua) -- A Japanese executive kidnapped by
five armed men has been released by the abductors after paying 3.7
million pesos (123,000 U.S. dollars) as the ransom, police said
here today.
</P>
<P>
Police said the Japanese was kidnapped when driving home aboard
a car along a highway in the village of Santa Rita, Bulacan
province, the northern Philippines on August 22.
</P>
<P>
The kidnappers demanded 20 million pesos, but after secret
talks between the kidnappers and the Japanese embassy personnel in
Manila, they were paid 3.7 million by the company the Japanese was
working for, police said. 
