<HEADLINE> New Company Group In Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, August 28 (Xinhua) -- The opening of the Lugang
(Railway and Port) Group Co. Ltd was announced in Nanning, the
capital of China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
It was founded by the Guangxi Local Railways Co. Ltd., the
Fangchenggang Port Administration, the State Assets Bureau of
Beihai City, and the Qinzhou Port Administration.
</P>
<P>
Qin Chenggong, Chairman of the Board of the group, said that
they will operate the new conglomerate in accordance with the
Corporate Law and the practices of a modern enterprise.
</P>
<P>
He said his conglomerate will choose only better quality assets
and form a joint-stock firm to be listed on the stock market to
raise more money for railway and port construction.
</P>
<P>
The new conglomerate has 3.4 billion yuan in registered
capital, 7,395 employees, and is becoming one of Guangxi's largest
companies.
</P>
<P>
Lugang Group now operates 307 km of railways and has an
additional 110 km still under construction. It also has 38 berths,
two of which are under construction, with a combined annual
handling capacity of 12 million tons. 
