<HEADLINE> Road Accidents Claim 521 in Zimbabwe This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Traffic accidents continue to be
among the major causes of death in Zimbabwe with a total of 521
people killed between January and June this year, a local daily,
The Herald, reported today.
</P>
<P>
Some 4,902 people were injured during the same period,
prompting police to increase road patrols.
</P>
<P>
Of the 7,791 accidents experienced since January this year,
5,327 were caused by lack of attention while driving and another
2,831 were caused by following other vehicles too closely.
</P>
<P>
Police said 392,349 accidents were recorded in this country
between 1980 and 1996, in which 17,721 people were killed while
some 201,877 people were seriously injured during that period.
</P>
<P>
Last year an average of 21 people were killed in accidents
country-wide each week, while an average of 49 were injured every
week during the same period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
