<HEADLINE> World Bank Finances Nepal's Agricultural Research </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
announced the approval of a 24.3 million U.S. dollar credit to
help meet the agriculture research and extension needs of the
Nepalese farmers.
</P>
<P>
The two-phased project over a period of five years will be
carried out in 31 districts to bring benefits to about 10
million farmers of the country.
</P>
<P>
The project is designed to enhance agricultural
productivity and increase rural incomes, employment and food
supply through improved service delivery systems.
</P>
<P>
The project will assist the Government of Nepal in improving
the management and capacity of agriculture research and extension
services by developing location-specific agriculture research
technologies on the basis of close consultations with local
farmers and by improving the technology delivery system.
</P>
<P>
The credit will be channeled through the International
Development Association (IDA), the World Bank's concessionary
lending wing for developing countries. 
</P>
