<P>
He said Bougainvilleans feel particularly comfortable with New
Zealand acting as host, anticipating MaKinnon would be received
with open arms when he visits the island Friday.
</P>
<P>
New Zealand brokered the peace talks last month, bringing
together the warring factions on the island torn by a civil war in
the last ten years. The talks ended with the signing of the
Burnham Declaration in which all factions pledged their commitment
to peace.
</P>
<P>
Apart from visiting Bougainville, MaKinnon will also hold the
formal annual meeting with Genia in an effort to further cement
the relationship between the two countries, NZPA said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
