<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine and Russia reached an
agreement here today on strengthening the work of the Military
Technological Subcommission.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was achieved when Ukrainain Prime Minister Valery
Pustovoitenko talked today with the visiting Russian Minister of
Defense, Ignor Sergeyev, who arrived Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The subcommission comes under the Ukrainian-Russia Joint
Commission.
</P>
<P>
During the talk, Sergeyev stressed that both sides should make
great efforts to boost the integration of the Defense Complex
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Ukrainian shipbuilding factories were working at top tempo to
fulfil contracts to build ships for the Russian fleet, said
Pustovoitenko.
</P>
<P>
However, a money shortage was affecting the modernization of
the Russian fleet code-named "Russia", and the building of other
missile cruisers, added the Ukrainian Prime Minister.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine and Russia should jointly build cruisers and build
ships for a third country, Pustovoitenko suggested.
</P>
<P>
Both sides agreed to speed up the signing of agreements on such
issues as the provision of hydrographic service to pilot ships,
and the use of radio transmission frequencies and space.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Defense Minister is scheduled to meet the Ukrainian
President Leonid Kuchma Thursday on the Crimean Peninsula where
the president is on holiday. 
