the Aral Sea is to improve the living conditions of the people in
the area, Kazakhstan Telegraph Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The consumption of the water resources should be managed,
salinization of the soil should be curbed and the local people
should be given drinking water and medicines, the president told
the chairman of an international fund for the Aral Sea, Rim
Giniyatullin.
</P>
<P>
He urged the implementation of rescue plans drawn up in the
past few years.
</P>
<P>
The Aral Sea, which borders Kazakhstan and Uzbekistan, has
shrunk by a half in area in the past three decades. Salt on the
dry lake-bed has caused severe pollution to water sources and
salinization of the soil. 
