<HEADLINE> Poland Gets $2 Billion Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Poland received 1.97 billion
U.S. dollars in overseas investments in the first half of this
year, driving the aggregate foreign investment since 1989 to 14
billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The State Foreign Investment Bureau also forecast another 2.2
billion dollars of capital inflow in the second half, which would
increase this year's foreign investment to 4.17 billion dollars.
</P>
