<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indo-Swiss Banks Launch "Fast Forex" in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 28 (Xinhua) -- India's Indusind Bank Ltd. has
tied up with the Swiss Bank Corporation to provide "fast forex"
service to its account holders across its branches in India,
official sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
By this arrangement, foreign remittance in and out of the
country will take only a matter of 55 seconds.
</P>
<P>
"Fast forex" stands for fully automated straight through forex,
which allows for a two-way communication system, whereby foreign
exchange remitted overseas or expected from overseas receives
immediate confirmation.
</P>
<P>
"You send your customer's money anywhere in the world and
before he finishes his cup of tea, the computer system would show
the actual movement of the transaction and get a confirmation
right away," said S.J. Vijay, Indusind's head of international
banking.
</P>
<P>
All the branches have been installed with the clearing house
interbank payment (CHIP) system in New York, which enables each
branch to see what is coming in and whether or not what is
supposed to go out has gone, Vijay said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
