<HEADLINE> Tianjin Encourages House Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, August 28 (Xinhua) -- North China's Tianjin encourages
the construction of residential apartments by forming housing
cooperatives to help raise required funds.
</P>
<P>
Sixteen of the city's 18 urban districts and suburban counties
have introduced the formation of housing cooperatives to build
more apartments to improve the living conditions of workers.
</P>
<P>
Government subsidies were previously used in urban areas to
build houses and apartments, which were then allocated as a form of
welfare.
</P>
<P>
The city's housing cooperatives raised 130 million Yuan from
individuals in the first seven months of this year, double the
figure for 1996.
</P>
<P>
The city is now building a floor space of 200,000 square
meters. Some 100,000 sq. m. will be completed this year and
allocated to more than 2,000 families. 
</P>
