<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Merapi Volcano Spews Tons of Lava </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Mount Merapi, an active volcano
located at the borderline of Central Java and Yogyakarta of
Indonesia, emits about 47 tons of hot lava and sulfuric gas per
day, according to a local press report today.
</P>
<P>
The lava flows can reach as far as 2.5 kilometers in distance,
the report quoted an official as saying.
</P>
<P>
The official warned that Merapi is on an alert status and local
residents should be ready to evacuate if major eruptions occur.
</P>
<P>
The steam clouds from the volcano can reach temperatures of 600
degrees Celsius and can descend at any time, destroying much of
what they come into contact with, experts said.
</P>
<P>
The local volcanology office says most of the lava has flowed
into rivers beneath the volcano, including the Krasak, Bebeng,
Senowo and Bojong.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
