<HEADLINE> Ecuador Seeking Peaceful Solution With Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Ecuadoran President Fabian
Alarcon said today that his country would support all necessary
efforts essential to reaching permanent, definitive and dignified
peace with Peru.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that war means victory for no one," Alarcon said,
adding that a war always leaves in its wake human casualties and
tremendous economic, social, political and moral consequences.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference held here today before ending his two-day
visit to Uruguay, The Ecuadoran president said his country hopes
Ecuador and Peru can find a definitive solution to their political
and social problems, which include poverty, unemployment and
homelessness.
</P>
<P>
Relations between Ecuador and Peru have been tense since the
two countries became enmeshed in a large-scale border conflict in
January 1995. Ceasefire was achieved 50 days later through the
mediation of the Rio De Janeiro Protocol countries, and the two
countries have since held two rounds of talks to try and solve the
conflict so far.
</P>
<P>
Alarcon said the third round of talks will be held in
September. 
</P>
