<HEADLINE> Ecuador, Uruguay Sign Cooperation Accords </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Uruguay`s President Julio
Maria Sanguinetti and his Ecuadorian counterpart Fabian Alarcon
inked here today three accords on fighting drug-trafficking and
enhancing cooperation in various fields.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents agreed that one of the most effective ways
to improve economic relations is to establish strategic alliances
between the business sectors of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
As to the creation of a free trade zone among members of Andean
Pact and the Southern Common Market, Sanguinetti and Alarcon said
they were determined to see it established before December 31,
1997.
</P>
<P>
They said establishing the America Free Trade Zone is a
suitable response to the trend of economic inter-dependence and
globalization.
</P>
<P>
They considered Latin American integration as a top issue and
stressed that the Association for Latin American Integration
should play a major role in fostering strategies aimed at
promoting regional, hemispheric and world commerce.
</P>
<P>
Alarcon, who arrived Tuesday in Uruguay for a two-day visit,
left this evening for home. 
</P>
