<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Costa Rica to Authorize Public Bank Auction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The Costa Rican government will
set a deadline for the Assembly to authorize the privatization of
the Banco de Costa Rica, the second largest bank in the country.
</P>
<P>
The public offer to bid for state-owned banks is intended to
raise money to reduce the country`s taxation deficit. But the plan
is opposed by various social groups.
</P>
<P>
The banking system, nationalized in 1948, has been the
foundation for the economic model in Costa Rica for nearly 50
years. Two days ago, the state's monopoly on banks and banking
changed drastically when banks were allowed to be privatized.
</P>
<P>
During President Jose Maria Figueres administration, Banco
Anglocostarricense, the oldest bank of Costa Rica, was closed due
to bankruptcy of overseas operations. Now only three public banks
and an international branch still operate.
</P>
<P>
The Costa Rican government is trying to pass a law to sell the
Banco de Costa Rica.
</P>
<P>
The Inter-American Development Bank has approved a loan for
Costa Rica to promote public biddings for its banks worldwide.
</P>
</TEXT>
