helping bringing another NBA championship to Chicago," Jordan said
in a statement released by the Bulls.
</P>
<P>
Jordan, who led Chicago Bulls to five NBA championships in
seven seasons, met with Bulls chairman Jerry Reinsdorf Tuesday in
Las Vegas, Neveva. His contract may worth 36 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
To resign Jordan, Bulls made a one-year deal with coach Phil
Jackson worth 6 million earlier this summer. But Jordan also
wanted to force Bulls to keep Scottie Pippen, whom the Bulls
intended to trade in June.
</P>
<P>
Pippen, 31, is likely to earn 2.7 million next season in the
final year of an eight-year contract. 
