<HEADLINE> Libyan Arrested for 1986 Berlin Disco Bombing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 27 (Xinhua) -- A Libyan wanted in connection with
the 1986 bombing of a Berlin discotheque frequented by U.S.
soldiers has been arrested in Rome, police said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A police spokesman said the Libyan, Musbah Abulghasem Eter, 40,
was arrested on Tuesday night by Italy's anti-terrorism squad,
which is known as DIGOS.
</P>
<P>
The disco bombing in then West Berlin killed two U.S. soldiers,
a Turkish woman, and injured more than 200 others, most of them
U.S. soldiers.
</P>
<P>
The United States blamed Libya for the blast, which prompted
the U.S. administration to order the bombing of Libya's two
largest cities in April 1986. 
