<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment Sparks Robust Growth in East China Port City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, August 28 (Xinhua) -- Statistics show that overseas
investment has greatly bolstered the economy of Quanzhou port city
in east China's Fujian province.
</P>
<P>
The city was home to 6,321 overseas-funded businesses by the
end of July. The industrial output value of these businesses
accounted for 34.93 percent of the city's total in July. The
proportion of their export volume to the city's total also rose
from 9.96 percent in 1985 to 89 percent.
</P>
<P>
Quanzhou, which approved its first foreign-funded business in
1981, continues to invest heavily in the construction of
expressways, power plants and other infrastructural facilities
to expand the port's accommodating capacity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
