<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cuban Police Raid Disco in Havana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, August 27 (Xinhua) -- Cuban police raided a gay disco
in Havana over the weekend, detaining 800 people for allegedly
promoting illegal activities, the National Police confirmed today.
</P>
<P>
Major Angel Diaz of the National Police said the people
arrested at the El Periquiton discotheque included prostitutes,
hustlers, minors and foreigners.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 2,000 U.S dollars and 30,000 Cuban pesos (officially
equal to 30,000 U.S. dollars) were confiscated during the raid.
</P>
<P>
Under the Cuban law, people convicted of engaging in businesses
that encourage illegal sexual activity will face up to five years
in prison. 
</P>
</TEXT>
