<HEADLINE> Dow Edges Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 27 (Xinhua) -- A late rebound lifted the stock
market to marginal gains today with the Dow Jones industrial
average edging up 5.11 points to 7,787.33, after recovering from
an 85-point slide.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by an 11-to-8 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, where NYSE volume totaling 492.09
million shares as against 449.08 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
Broad-market measures also turned higher as bonds rebounded
from an afternoon slide.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 0.68 to 913.70, the
NYSE composite index rose 0.69 to 476.05, and the Nasdaq composite
index rose 4.24 to 1,595.54
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 rose 2.53 to 420.84, edging Aug.'s record
close of 420.73.
</P>
<P>
The American Stock Exchange composite index, which has a large
constituency of smaller-company stocks, rose 3.82 to 651.12, about
3 points shy of record territory.
</P>
<P>
Before today, the Dow had fallen for four consecutive sessions,
losing about 240 points, or 3 percent, over that span. The average
of 30 big companies still stands nearly 500 points shy of its
record high of 8,259.31 set earlier this month.  
</P>
