<HEADLINE> Quesada Snatches Universiade Triple Jump Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Italy, August 27 (Xinhua) -- The Athen world championships
gold medallist Yoelbi Quesada of Cuba beat his compatriot Aliecer
Urrutia and other rivals to snatch the men's triple jump gold medal at
the 19th World University Games here on Wednesday evening.
</P>
<P>
Quesada, also ranked first in the world this year, cleared 17.35
meters in the 4th attempt.
</P>
<P>
Urrutia, world championships bronze medallist, took the silver with
17.11 meters and American Robert Howard was third with 17.08 meters.
</P>
<P>
Russian Natalia Sadova, Olympic silver medal winner and world
championships bronze medallist, won the women's discus throw gold
medal with a throw of 67.02 meters. the silver and bronze medals went
to Chinese Hu Honglian (61.00m) and Romanian Nicoletta Grasu (60.08m).
</P>
<P>
Russia also picked up other two golds. Andrei Kislykh clocked 13.44
seconds for the men's 110m hurdles champion, belgian Jonathan Nsenga
was the runner-up in 13.51 seconds and American Dudley Dorival came
third with 13.53 seconds.
</P>
<P>
In the women's 200m race, Ekaterina Lechtcheva of Russia won the
gold in 23.18 seconds, followed by Katia Benth of France in 23.11
and bulgarian Monika Gatchevska in 23.60.
</P>
<P>
The women's heptathlon champion went to Mona Steigauf of Germany
who totalled 6,546 points after seven events of competition. Russian
Irina Vostrikova finished second in 6,175 points and Marie Collonville
of France was third in 6,143 point.
</P>
<P>
In the men's 200m event, the Americans finished one-two with
Gentry Bradley winning the gold in 20.48 seconds and Anthony Wheeler
taking silver in 20.64 while Anninos Marcoullides of Cyprus got the
bronze in 20.72.
</P>
<P>
The third day competition of the Universiade athletics on Thursday
will produce seven gold medals on offer.  
</P>
</TEXT>
