<HEADLINE> Security Council Condemns Genocide of Congo Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS August 27 (Xinhua) -- The Security Council of
the United Nations today condemned the recent genocide of 148
Congolese refugees in Rwanda, stressing that those who are
responsible for the genocide should brought to the justice.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the reporters, Security Council President John
Weston of Britain said :"My colleagues want me to emphasize that
we all condemn the killing of the 148 Congolese refugees at
Mudende refugee camp in Rwanda."
</P>
<P>
"We endorse the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees's
call for an end to this spiral of violence in parts of the Great
Lakes region. We welcome the High Commissioner's decision to
dispatch teams to screen the Rwandan refugees in 10 African
countries. We called on the host countries to cooperate with the
High Commissioner to ensure protection for genuine refugees and
that those who may be guilty of genocide in Rwanda are brought to
justice," said Weston.
</P>
<P>
The refugees killed last Friday were mainly ethnic Tutsis from
former Zaire, now called the Democratic Republic of Congo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
